Vyges Metadata Specification
Copyright 2025 Vyges Inc.

This product includes software developed by Vyges Inc. (https://vyges.com).

Contributors:
- Shivaram Mysore (shivaram@vyges.com) - Primary author and maintainer

This specification defines a standardized JSON Schema format for describing 
reusable silicon IP blocks, enabling automated discovery, integration, and 
management of hardware IP across different design flows and platforms.

For more information about this project, visit:
https://github.com/vyges/vyges-metadata-spec

PATENT NOTICE:
Vyges Inc. has filed provisional patent applications covering the Vyges 
ecosystem architecture - the specific methodology for IP discovery, 
metadata management, template integration, and automated workflow 
orchestration.

This patent filing does NOT affect:
- Use of Vyges IP templates (Apache 2.0 licensed)
- Use of Vyges-generated IP blocks (Apache 2.0 licensed)
- Creation of your own IP blocks and metadata formats
- Use of standard EDA tools and workflows

This patent filing DOES protect:
- The specific Vyges architectural methodology
- The integrated workflow from IP creation to deployment
- The ecosystem design and integration approach

